                <h1>The Evolution of the Constitution: A Brief History</h1>
                <p>The history of the constitution reflects the evolution of governance and individual rights. Originating with the Magna Carta in 1215, it laid the groundwork for modern democracies. The U.S. Constitution, established in 1787, further shaped governance, introducing checks and balances. Amendments evolved to protect civil liberties, ensuring a living document that adapts to societal changes.</p>
